  "difficulty": "Medium",
  "markdown_debrief": "### SHARP 4.0 Cognitive & Surgical Debrief\n\n> **💡 3 cm breast mass, no nodes, no mets = T2N0M0.**\n\n---\n\n## S — Set the Stage\nThe correct answer is E, T2N0M0. This staging accurately reflects a 3 cm breast mass (T2), with no palpable axillary nodes (N0), and no clinical evidence of distant metastasis (M0).\n\n## H — Highlight Excellence\nThe TNM staging system is a critical tool for classifying cancer extent, guiding treatment, and predicting prognosis. For breast cancer, 'T' describes the primary tumor size, 'N' describes regional lymph node involvement, and 'M' indicates distant metastasis. A tumor between 2 cm and 5 cm is classified as T2. The absence of palpable axillary nodes clinically indicates N0, and no clinical evidence of metastasis indicates M0. Accurate clinical assessment is paramount for initial staging.\n\n## A — Address the Gaps\n\nOption A (Incorrect): T1 is incorrect for a 3 cm mass, and N1/M1 are incorrect as there are no palpable nodes or distant metastasis.\nOption B (Incorrect): T1 is incorrect as a 3 cm mass falls into the T2 category.\nOption C (Incorrect): N2 is incorrect as there are no palpable axillary nodes, let alone fixed/matted ones.\nOption D (Incorrect): N1 is incorrect as there are no palpable axillary nodes.\n\n## R — Review Learning Points\n\n| T Category | Tumor Size/Description |\n|---|---|\n| T1 | Tumor ≤ 2 cm |\n| T2 | Tumor > 2 cm but ≤ 5 cm |\n| T3 | Tumor > 5 cm |\n| T4 | Tumor of any size with direct extension to chest wall or skin, or inflammatory breast cancer |\n\n## P — Plan (Board Pearl)\nBoard Pearl: TNM: Tumor Size, Nodes, Metastasis. Memorize the T-size cutoffs!\n\n---\n\n## 🔬 Imaging & Intraoperative Pearl\nOn imaging (mammogram, ultrasound, MRI), the 3 cm mass would be clearly delineated, and careful ultrasound of the axilla would confirm the absence of suspicious lymph nodes to support the cN0 designation. PET/CT or bone scan would be used to rule out distant metastasis.\n\n## 📋 Guideline Anchor\nAJCC Cancer Staging Manual, 8th Edition (2017). This manual provides the definitive criteria for TNM staging across all cancer types, including breast cancer, which are essential for consistent classification and treatment planning.\n\n---\n\n### Answer Breakdown\n| Option | Text | Status |\n|--------|------|--------|\n| A | T1N1M1 | ❌ Incorrect |\n| B | T1N0M0 | ❌ Incorrect |\n| C | T2N2M0 | ❌ Incorrect |\n| D | T2N1M0 | ❌ Incorrect |\n| E | T2N0M0 | ✅ Correct |\n\n**✅ Answer: E) ** &nbsp;|&nbsp; **Difficulty: Medium** &nbsp;|&nbsp; **Source: 872068331-Surgery-MCQs.txt**\n",
