  "question": "A 29-year-old woman is referred by her doctor with a 3-month history of a painless lump in the anterior aspect of the neck. She does not describe any hoarseness of voice. Examination reveals a lump in the left anterior triangle, which moves up and down with swallowing. FNA cytology of the lump reveals nuclear grooves and Psamomma's bodies. What is the most likely diagnosis?",
